     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="255"/>
   <pb n="489" facs="255"/>
   <opener>
      <salute>READERS▪</salute>
   </opener>
   <p>GIve me leave to performe a necessary du<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ty,
which my affection owes to the bles<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>
      <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ed
memory of that reverend Prelate, my much
<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>onoured Friend, Doctor <hi>Ailmer▪</hi> Hee was
one, whose life and death made as full and per<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fect
a Story of worth and goodnesse, as earth
would suffer, and whose pregnant vertues de<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>serve
as faithfull a Register as earth can keepe:
In whose happy remembrance, I have here
<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="2 letters">
         <desc>••</desc>
      </gap>usted these Elegies to Time and your favours:
Had he bin a Lampe to light me alone, my pri<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>
      <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ate
griefes had beene sufficient; but being a
Sunne, whose beames reflected on all; all have
<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> interest in his memory: To which end I re<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>commend
these memorialls to the publike, in
testimony of my undissembled affection,
and true pietie that I owe to so great
an example of Vertue and
Learning.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>F. Q.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
